Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Mt. Whitney
Description: Tallest peak in my city: San Marcos, California. Located in the Cerro De Los Posas hill range. Popular for hiking and mountain biking in the lovely chaparall environment.

Name: Point Conception Lighthouse
Description: A historic lighthouse located at Point Conception, California. Point conception is the point where the Southern and Central coasts meet, also where the coast (going north) switches from having the ocean to the south, back to the ocean being to the west. The lighthouse is currently under US Military occupation and inaccessible to the public.

Name: USS Midway Museum Parking Lot/Dock
Description: The parking lot for the USS Midway Museum in Downtown San Diego. It is also a dock right on the water, perfect views of the bay, especially for sunsets.

Name: Cold Spring Canyon Arch Bridge
Description: A bridge spanning two mountains on the San Marcos pass connecting Santa Barbara with Chumash territory and Solvang. The bridge is an Arch bridge and is green.

Name: Battery Spencer
Description: Location for coastal defense guns, this remains of a post Civil War battery is one of the best spots to view the Golden gate Bridge
